# **The Power of Healthy Mindsets**

Just like engines provide power to propel cars, your mindsets provide power to propel your life.

Whether consciously or unconsciously, mindsets dictate how you live your life. And, like engines, they are often hidden underneath layers of grease and dirt. Busy activities of today and emotional pressures of work drown out the sputtering mindsets powering your life.

## **Mindsets Will Influence Your Success**

Unless you learn how to pay attention to your mindsets, you will become victim to them. You might unknowingly surrender the helpful ones or be held back by the harmful ones. However, by paying careful attention to these powerful tools, you can leverage them to your advantage.

You interpret what is friend or foe through your mindsets. Like it or not, you subconsciously guard yourself against any situation which challenges your existing mindset.

If you believe you were born to lose, you will find yourself sabotaging your own success. If you do happen to succeed, you will conclude it was by accident, because actual success would conflict with your underlying mindset.

This is why you must pay attention to your mindsets.

## **Uncovering Hidden Mindsets**

Are you aware of what you're thinking right now?

Perhaps your friends are pursuing their dreams and advancing their careers, but you find yourself thinking:

1. I don't have enough money to pursue my dreams.  
2. I'm too busy to pursue my dreams.  
3. My dreams are not that important.  
4. I'm not smart enough to pursue my dreams.

Or, maybe you just received a new promotion you’re thinking thoughts like:

*“I hope nobody finds out that I'm not good enough.”*

*“I have no idea what to do here.”*

*“If I make a mistake, I'll completely blow it.”*

The irony is you would never make these statements about your friends, yet you willingly make them about yourself. 

These mindsets are holding you back from reaching your full potential. 

Many people think they must achieve their dreams to convince themselves of truth. They don’t realizing they must first *believe* the truth before they can ever achieve their dreams.

Destructive thoughts aren't always conscious. They often lurk in the back of your mind, sticking their heads out only occasionally to tell you to quit trying to be successful. You might not be aware of them but you can observe their work in your life.

If you are having trouble achieving your dream, you likely have a few of these unhealthy mindsets hampering your power. You have to scare them out of the darkness into the light, where you can--and must--completely demolish them.
